1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,480
Take a closer look.

2
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:15,640
This is the genuine piece
straight from the palace.

3
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:17,280
Look at those brushstrokes.

4
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,690
It's the calligraphy by Zhu Zhishan,

5
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,680
one of the Four Great Masters
of the Ming Dynasty.

6
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,480
Officers.

7
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:29,160
Officers,

8
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:29,680
you...

9
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:30,560
Are you Master Song?

10
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:31,720
I am.

11
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,760
=Cases Between Us=
What's the matter?

12
00:00:33,776 --> 00:00:34,600
Nobody move.

13
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,360
Seal the shop.

14
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,860
=Episode 6=

15
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:45,440
Move everything out.

16
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,840
I'll examine every piece myself.

17
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:48,900
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

18
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:49,680
Move.

19
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:53,280
Young Master Zhao.

20
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:54,840
Young Master Zhao,

21
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,480
we're in the same business.

22
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:58,240
We'll see each other often.

23
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:01,360
Please cut me some slack.

24
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:02,240
Master Song,

25
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,800
let me teach you an English phrase.

26
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:10,560
No.

27
00:01:17,872 --> 00:01:19,680
You're using this
to settle a personal score.

28
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,560
A personal score?

29
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:22,920
This is a national score.

30
00:01:23,310 --> 00:01:25,350
Do you know how many antiques
he's sold to foreigners

31
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:25,960
over the years?

32
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:27,760
I begged him

33
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:29,920
to let me see the good pieces first.

34
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:30,896
You know what he did?

35
00:01:30,928 --> 00:01:32,790
He teamed up with those foreigners
to swindle me.

36
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,910
How could I let this slide?

37
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,960
Last time, I sold him a fake antique
I made myself.

38
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,920
Yet he hasn't learned his lesson.
This time, I'll catch him!

39
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,144
So people will think twice before
selling our treasures to foreigners.

40
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,160
That's why he said

41
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,480
you tricked him

42
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,560
back in the alley?

43
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,440
My craftsmanship is exceptional.

44
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:49,360
And that's not all.

45
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,640
Master Song deals
in tomb robbing and stolen goods.

46
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,920
I've got witnesses and evidence.

47
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,600
Then why didn't you report him before?

48
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,800
Because I hadn't met

49
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,360
a righteous police officer yet.

50
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,080
Enough with the flattery.

51
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,544
So from now on,

52
00:02:02,544 --> 00:02:04,010
can I come to you if I need something?

53
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:05,140
For the country and justice,

54
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,550
a good officer won't turn it down.

55
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,720
Listen to what you said.

56
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:08,320
So,

57
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:08,720
what about

58
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,320
my request?

59
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,000
I kept my promise.

60
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:15,800
What about you?

61
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,120
Relax.

62
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,880
Almost there.

63
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,440
Chief Yuan,

64
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:24,520
this way.

65
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,760
Your family sure has pocketed a lot.

66
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,640
Family inheritance.

67
00:02:34,032 --> 00:02:34,880
Please have a seat.

68
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,800
Serve tea for Chief Yuan.

69
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,520
Tea dust.

70
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:48,688
As much as you want.

71
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,200
What's that?

72
00:02:54,256 --> 00:02:57,280
We ought to leave some evidence behind
while the investigation is underway.

73
00:02:57,290 --> 00:02:58,700
Just in case
the papers run the story again

74
00:02:58,710 --> 00:02:59,870
without a single picture of me.

75
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:02,200
Then, when reporters ask,
I'm invisible all over again.

76
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,120
I knew you were up to no good.

77
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,000
You said you'd help me,

78
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,080
but all you really wanted
was to get in the papers.

79
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,720
That's a bit harsh.

80
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,480
You want to solve the case.

81
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,520
I've got the leads.

82
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,480
It's a win-win.

83
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:26,720
Smile.

84
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,520
Otherwise, people will say

85
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,680
the police aren't approachable.

86
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,240
Chest out.

87
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:30,920
Chin up.

88
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:31,520
Turn a little.

89
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,480
Three, two, one. Cheese.

90
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,800
Can we get to the point now?

91
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,000
What was Beijing called before?

92
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,600
Jingshi.

93
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,080
Before that.

94
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,600
Yuandadu.

95
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,320
Earlier.

96
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:52,400
Before the Qin Dynasty.

97
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,440
Youzhou.

98
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:55,360
Exactly.

99
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,120
Youzhou.

100
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,600
Legend says

101
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:06,160
an evil dragon once terrorized Youzhou,

102
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,400
and the people suffered terribly.

103
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,040
They had no choice

104
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,080
but to flee into the western

105
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,960
and northern mountains.

106
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,680
When Nezha heard about it,

107
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,600
he rode in on his Fire Wheels,

108
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,400
wielding his weapons,

109
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:20,800
and battled the dragon
for eighty-one days.

110
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,440
Finally, he subdued the beast.

111
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,000
After that,

112
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:24,960
the floodwaters receded,

113
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:27,024
and the people of Youzhou
could finally live in peace.

114
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,160
Thousands of years later,

115
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,960
after Zhu Di won the Jingnan campaign

116
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,160
and moved the capital here,

117
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,960
he decided to rebuild Beijing.

118
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,200
So he summoned Liu Bowen

119
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,080
and Yao Guangxiao to design the city.

120
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,200
One was his strategist,
the other his adviser.

121
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,120
The two always fought
and never saw eye to eye.

122
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,600
Can you skip to the point?

123
00:04:45,856 --> 00:04:46,640
Anyway,

124
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
they each drew up a plan

125
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,528
for Zhu Di.

126
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,560
When Zhu Di saw them, he laughed.

127
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,600
Both had come up
with the exact same layout

128
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,440
to suppress the Dragon King.

129
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,480
That design

130
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,680
later became known as...

131
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,600
the Eight-Armed Nezha City.

132
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:08,000
(Latest Detailed Map of Beijing)

133
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,680
The four east gates
and the four west gates

134
00:05:09,690 --> 00:05:10,680
form Nezha's eight arms.

135
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,896
The two northern gates,
Desheng Gate and Anding Gate,

136
00:05:12,928 --> 00:05:14,520
are his feet.

137
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:16,080
Zhengyang Gate in the south

138
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,440
is his head.

139
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,840
Put them together, and you get...

140
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,920
The Eight-Armed Nezha.

141
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,440
When Yao Guangxiao saw Liu Bowen's plan,

142
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,600
he joked,

143
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,280
"Your Nezha has eight arms,

144
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,840
but no organs."

145
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:33,360
Liu Bowen smiled,
fanned himself, and said,

146
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,560
"The square Imperial City

147
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,080
is Nezha's vital organs.

148
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,440
The Meridian Gate is the mouth.

149
00:05:39,504 --> 00:05:41,160
From the Meridian Gate to Zhengyang Gate

150
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,440
is the head,

151
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,640
and the long avenue between them

152
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:46,400
is the esophagus.

153
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,840
Of course,

154
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:49,200
that's just a folk legend,

155
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,120
not true history.

156
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:50,800
Liu Bowen died

157
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,720
during the Hongwu era.

158
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,880
People later

159
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,280
embellished the story.

160
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,080
But Beijing's layout

161
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,720
barely changed after the Ming Dynasty

162
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,520
until the Republic.

163
00:05:59,040 --> 00:05:59,880
Chief,

164
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,560
something happened.

165
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,000
What is it?

166
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,760
Someone trashed your car.

167
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:12,980
(Jingshi Police Department)

168
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,440
Good grief.

169
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,440
The windshield's smashed.

170
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:21,440
What happened?

171
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,720
It's a Molotov cocktail.

172
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,320
Chief Yuan spent

173
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,840
two months' salary

174
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:25,920
modifying it.

175
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,960
Inline-four engine,

176
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,160
double overhead camshaft,

177
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,040
and sixteen valves.

178
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,360
It's one of a kind in Beijing.

179
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,160
It makes chasing crooks a lot easier.

180
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,560
Don't be mad.

181
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,200
I'll get you a German car.

182
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:41,940
(Jingshi Police Department)

183
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:48,280
That's everything. There's nothing else.

184
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,200
Stay still.

185
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,640
(Director Zheng)
Do you know,

186
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,840
(of the Tram Company)
damaging police property can get you

187
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:54,760
at least three months in prison?

188
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,120
Did I say you could move?

189
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,440
Stay still!

190
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:58,960
Chief.

191
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,200
Nephew!

192
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,640
What are you doing here?

193
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,000
Seventh Uncle?

194
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:09,840
Wait.

195
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,000
Why are you here?

196
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,400
Did your child go missing too?

197
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,760
What are you talking about?

198
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,240
This is Zheng,

199
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,560
head of the tram company.

200
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:23,920
By family rank,
he calls my mother Grandmother,

201
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,760
and me Uncle.

202
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,320
This is Yuan Hong. Chief Yuan.

203
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,400
Chief Yuan.

204
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:30,040
Did you smash his car?

205
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,320
Why did you do that?

206
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,480
My grandson's been missing.

207
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,040
There's no news at all.

208
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:38,920
Wouldn't you be anxious

209
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,040
if it were your family?

210
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,600
Of course we are.

211
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,720
Eleven children disappeared

212
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,960
at Beihai Park last night.

213
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,200
Eleven?

214
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,240
Why aren't you doing anything?

215
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,640
Who says we weren't?

216
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,930
We were discussing
the Eight-Armed Nezha theory.

217
00:07:50,944 --> 00:07:52,320
We were mapping out Beijing.

218
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,760
Then your incident interrupted us.

219
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,200
Fine. We'll keep you in the loop.

220
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,536
Give us some time to investigate.

221
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,800
You?

222
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,240
Is he a cop now?

223
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,440
I help Chief Yuan as a consultant.

224
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,040
A...

225
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,840
consultant?

226
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,520
Stop kidding.

227
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,688
Couldn't you find someone else?

228
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:10,520
Three generations, only one son each.

229
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,280
Don't let my grandson be the one
who ends it.

230
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:14,280
You hired him as a consultant?

231
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,040
Looking down on me?

232
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,720
He...

233
00:08:15,808 --> 00:08:17,712
If you look down on me,
then solve it yourself.

234
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,480
Lives are at stake.

235
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,040
This isn't a joke.

236
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,040
Don't worry.

237
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,248
As long as the child is alive,

238
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,280
we'll bring him back.

239
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,680
You mean he could be dead?

240
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,600
If he's dead,

241
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,520
the police department...

242
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:31,160
- Calm down! Clam down!
- You should do something. What do I do?

243
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,320
We'll handle it. If manpower

244
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,920
isn't enough, money will be. I'll put up

245
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,500
a reward of ten thousand silver coins.

246
00:08:35,616 --> 00:08:37,056
The whole city will help find him.

247
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:43,920
Yunkai,

248
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,120
take him to deal with the car.

249
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:46,760
Yes, sir.

250
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,720
Get up.

251
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,760
Give that back later.

252
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,840
Take it.

253
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,160
Take it back.

254
00:09:02,112 --> 00:09:03,536
Once Beijing's layout was altered,

255
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:04,470
its feng shui was broken.

256
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,290
Even Nezha can't keep it
under control anymore.

257
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,840
You believe in feng shui?

258
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,160
Antique dealers sometimes
deal with burial sites.

259
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,320
We have to know a little.

260
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,800
Have you noticed

261
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,840
what these families have

262
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,920
in common?

263
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,040
The power company,

264
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:20,880
the railway bureau,
and the tram company.

265
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:23,360
What major constructions

266
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,160
are underway these days?

267
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,000
(Morning Newspaper)
Jingshi's feng shui was severely damaged.

268
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,160
Who's to blame for
the Ghost Festival burning?

269
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,560
Last year,

270
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,760
the power company
shortened its cable routes.

271
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:42,520
Earlier this year, the railway bureau
straightened its tracks.

272
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,600
And recently, the tram company

273
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,840
started laying streetcar lines.

274
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,600
They all did the same thing.

275
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,480
Construction.

276
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,816
They tore down those pailou.
[*Monumental archway]

277
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,120
The power company

278
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,840
removed the two western pailou.

279
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:56,710
The railway bureau demolished
the southern ones.

280
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:59,344
Is the tram company planning
to tear down the eastern pailou, too?

281
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,960
Once the murders happened,
the site was sealed off,

282
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,440
and the projects stopped.

283
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,040
That's right.

284
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,712
Someone's trying to stir up public panic

285
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,720
by making people believe

286
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,912
that tearing down those pailou
damaged Jingshi's feng shui

287
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,840
and brought disaster to the city.

288
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,880
That would put the projects on hold

289
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:13,800
for a new review.

290
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,360
Getting them approved again
won't be easy.

291
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,720
We've figured out the motive.

292
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,800
Now we'll find the culprit.

293
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:24,880
Yang Shicheng from Yenching University.

294
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,000
Isn't that your alma mater?

295
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,040
You'd better brace yourself.

296
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,040
He's a tough nut.

297
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:33,760
Don't break your teeth on him.

298
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,040
Everyone,

299
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:38,080
we've won a major victory
in stopping the capitalists

300
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,240
from destroying

301
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,440
our cultural heritage.

302
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,040
(Yang Shicheng)
The pailou demolition has been suspended!

303
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:48,800
- Well done!
- Bravo!

304
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,840
Today it's a pailou.

305
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,040
Tomorrow it'll be the imperial palace.

306
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,040
They're not just tearing down a pailou.

307
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,280
They're tearing down five thousand years

308
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,360
of Chinese civilization.

309
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,600
Everyone,

310
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,400
can we

311
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,200
let that happen?

312
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:07,480
- No!
- No!

313
00:11:08,731 --> 00:11:10,575
Can we stand by

314
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,760
and let those greedy capitalists

315
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,120
do whatever they want?

316
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:17,480
- No!
- No!

317
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,560
Let me say a few words.

318
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:21,840
What's he doing here?

319
00:11:22,512 --> 00:11:23,744
(If a pailou falls,
our fortune also falls.)

320
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,000
Shicheng,

321
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,600
what do you think
of the pailou in Zanhua Alley?

322
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:32,544
The base is exquisitely carved,

323
00:11:32,576 --> 00:11:34,400
and the calligraphy
is bold and magnificent.

324
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,448
It's a remarkable place
of historic architecture.

325
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,000
It certainly has history.

326
00:11:39,616 --> 00:11:41,240
It was built during the Shunzhi's reign.

327
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:43,440
Duoduo, Prince Yu, slaughtered
countless Han people

328
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,848
and was rewarded with that pailou.

329
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,280
To the Qing nobility,
it was a military achievement

330
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,040
and honor.

331
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,080
But to the eight hundred thousand
innocent Han people,

332
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:52,920
it was a massacre,

333
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,120
and a scar.

334
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:56,600
History always has two sides.

335
00:11:56,672 --> 00:11:58,040
It depends on which side you're on.

336
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:04,840
Everyone,

337
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,760
he's twisting the issue.

338
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,400
Young Master Zhao,

339
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,184
with your talent
for turning black into white,

340
00:12:11,232 --> 00:12:13,030
I suppose you've picked up
quite a few bargains

341
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,160
in Liulichang Antique Market.

342
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,160
What do you mean?

343
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,000
Do you know this?

344
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,960
Whenever Young Master Zhao
sets his sights on something,

345
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,320
he spreads rumors that it's stolen

346
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,440
or a fake,

347
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,880
and then buys it after the price drops.

348
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,920
Mr. Zhang's

349
00:12:29,984 --> 00:12:31,640
rubbing of "Quick Snow and Clear Skies"

350
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,200
and Mr. Li's Xuande incense burner

351
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,280
both ended up in
his collection that way.

352
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:38,550
He's a profiteer.

353
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,320
I was stopping them
from selling to foreigners.

354
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:50,840
What a noble excuse.

355
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,040
Everything you saved

356
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,320
ended up decorating your house.

357
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,240
You wave the flag of patriotism

358
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,840
while taking what you want.

359
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:01,160
How can someone like him
talk about justice?

360
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,800
- Exactly.
- Exactly.

361
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,640
Is that how you all see me?

362
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,920
- Yes!
- Yes!

363
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,440
What else?

364
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:13,480
Of course.

365
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,600
You throw your weight around
because of your family.

366
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:18,760
Do you think we can't see that?

367
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,880
What we scholars despise most

368
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,440
are people like you.

369
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,640
Thieves dressed up as men of culture.

370
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:40,320
- Thief!
- Thief!

371
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,120
Back up!

372
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:42,920
Stop taking pictures.

373
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,480
Who are you? What gives you the right
to take our cameras?

374
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,960
I'm not just taking your cameras.

375
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,920
I'm taking you, too.

376
00:13:49,056 --> 00:13:50,944
Who are you? What right
do you have to arrest me?

377
00:13:51,056 --> 00:13:53,648
Yuan Hong, Division Four Chief
of the Jingshi Police Department.

378
00:13:53,968 --> 00:13:56,032
Where were you
between six and ten last night?

379
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,640
Why should I tell you?

380
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:02,360
Because of this.

381
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:04,960
Someone saw you

382
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,000
enter a Taoist temple
on Dongsi Alley yesterday.

383
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,200
You went in empty-handed.

384
00:14:08,272 --> 00:14:09,200
You came out carrying

385
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,360
talisman paper, cinnabar, lamp oil,

386
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:12,000
and flint.

387
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,680
What? Do you want to make elixirs?

388
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,320
Yang Dezhi.

389
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:16,720
Yes, sir.

390
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,240
Take him away.

391
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:18,400
Move.

392
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,040
The rally is over.

393
00:14:21,088 --> 00:14:22,080
Everyone, disperse.

394
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:25,480
Show's over. Move along.

395
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,040
Unbelievable.

396
00:14:43,152 --> 00:14:44,680
Why are you still taking pictures?

397
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,160
Oh.

398
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,360
What a daft.

399
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,480
(Interrogation Room)
The law tolerates no deception.

400
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:03,720
Fine-sounding words.

401
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,760
Do the police arrest people
without evidence now?

402
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,200
Eleven people died at the same time.

403
00:15:09,328 --> 00:15:10,720
You think I have doppelgangers?

404
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,120
You could've hired people.

405
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,240
I'm a poor student.

406
00:15:16,656 --> 00:15:17,888
I can barely afford tuition.

407
00:15:17,904 --> 00:15:19,700
Then why was a student like you
at the temple?

408
00:15:19,744 --> 00:15:20,480
I went to pray.

409
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:22,840
Is that a crime?

410
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,040
Why did you pray?

411
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,240
That's my freedom.

412
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:26,880
A knife can kill.

413
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:27,400
Can you prove

414
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,392
that everyone who buys a knife
is a murderer?

415
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:30,680
Use your brain.

416
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:31,560
Chief,

417
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:32,840
I can't take this anymore.

418
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:33,840
Keep talking tough,

419
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,008
and I'll make you regret it.

420
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,320
Go ahead. Beat me to death.

421
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:40,360
I'm just a student.

422
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,280
I have nothing but my integrity.

423
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:45,800
Since ancient times, all men must die.

424
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,360
Let me leave behind a loyal heart
to shine in history.

425
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,600
If my death

426
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,840
can awaken the people

427
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,160
and bring even a little justice

428
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,760
to this country,

429
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,520
I'll die without regret.

430
00:15:57,888 --> 00:15:58,920
You're a murder suspect,

431
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,530
and you have no shame reciting poetry?

432
00:16:00,544 --> 00:16:01,280
I've had enough.

433
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,360
Mom!

434
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,360
The police are beating me!

435
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:04,800
The police are beating me!

436
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:05,720
I'm reporting you!

437
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,760
I'm reporting you for police brutality!

438
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:11,800
The police are beating me!

439
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,800
The police...

440
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:17,080
Done shouting?

441
00:16:22,976 --> 00:16:24,600
I thought you were a student activist.

442
00:16:25,184 --> 00:16:26,416
Where's all that integrity now?

443
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:28,688
Ready to die for the great cause?
Die bravely with courage?

444
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:30,560
Chief,

445
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,640
we've got a new lead.

446
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:37,680
Go.

447
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,000
What did you find?

448
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:42,040
This was found in Yang Shicheng's dorm.

449
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:45,000
It's the newspaper.

450
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,120
(Morning Newspaper)

451
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,200
Notice anything different?

452
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:49,400
The papers are different.

453
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:50,320
Exactly.

454
00:16:50,784 --> 00:16:53,160
The one from Yang Shicheng's dorm
is printed on Xuan paper.

455
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,040
It's a proof copy from
before publication.

456
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,160
So?

457
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,400
So,

458
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:00,416
the Morning Newspaper goes to print
at four in the morning.

459
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,360
The murders happened
around ten last night.

460
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,680
For Jiuyue Press

461
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:04,800
to put it

462
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,200
on the front page,

463
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,000
they had to write the story

464
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:08,880
within six hours.

465
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:10,720
Only the publisher

466
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:11,840
or someone from Jiuyue Press

467
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,840
could've gotten an advance proof.

468
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,160
Yang Shicheng isn't
a member of Jiuyue Press.

469
00:17:16,304 --> 00:17:17,640
Which means only one possibility.

470
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:18,800
Last night,

471
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,680
he was with someone from Jiuyue Press.

472
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:21,680
Right.

473
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:23,880
Chief Yuan,

474
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,760
leave this to me.

475
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,200
I know how to deal

476
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,040
with people like him.

477
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,040
Shicheng.

478
00:17:40,736 --> 00:17:41,840
What are you doing here?

479
00:17:42,740 --> 00:17:46,100
(End of Episode 6)

480
00:17:46,561 --> 00:17:48,201
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

481
00:17:48,201 --> 00:17:49,741
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

482
00:17:49,741 --> 00:17:50,991
♪However, the world changes♪

483
00:17:50,991 --> 00:17:52,911
♪You'll still be by my side♪

484
00:17:52,911 --> 00:17:54,601
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

485
00:17:54,601 --> 00:17:56,171
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

486
00:17:56,171 --> 00:17:57,741
♪If this is my final chapter♪

487
00:17:57,741 --> 00:18:00,241
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
